Smoky, tangy, and creamy are the hallmarks of this delicious and quick (20-minute!) pasta. You'll toss sautéed dark meat chicken and zucchini with al dente penne in a tangy lemon cream sauce swirled with smoky mustard. Finish with a squeeze of fresh lemon juice and shower of fresh green chives, and dig right in!

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Pasta ==

Bring a #medium pot{} of @water{} with @salt{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-thick half-moons. Quarter @lemon{1}. Finely chop @chives{¼%oz}.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%oz} or cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

== Chicken ==

While pasta cooks, open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and almost cooked through, ~{3%minutes}.

Add zucchini and cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is lightly browned and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Swap in asparagus or broccoli for zucchini. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are lightly browned and chicken is cooked through, 3-5 minutes for asparagus or 4-5 minutes for broccoli.

== Mustard Cream Sauce ==

While chicken mixture cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @smoky mustard{1%oz}, @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1⁄2 cup reserved pasta cooking water, and juice from one lemon wedge (3⁄4 cup pasta cooking water and juice from two lemon wedges for 4 servings).

> If pasta isn't done cooking, ladle water directly from pot.

== Finishing ==

Reduce heat under pan with chicken mixture to low and stir in mustard sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until warmed through and thoroughly combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained pasta to pan; toss to thoroughly coat. Taste and add a squeeze of lemon juice; season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between #shallow bowls{} and top with chives. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.